 Business Briefs
																								 New Delhi, Oct. 29: Maruti Suzuki will invest $1.8 billion in the next four to five years to set up a research and development unit at Manesar and expand marketing and production. The company said this investment is in addition to Rs 9,000 crore it has committed to invest in the country. The company also announced a top management rejig. Managing director Jagdish Khattar will retire on December 18. 																								 Mumbai, Oct. 29: The government is planning to relax external commercial borrowing (ECB) norms, especially for increasing investment in infrastructure. ECB norms will be relaxed...But when we do it I cannot say ... The norms for the infrastructure sector will be relaxed at the earliest, finance secretary D. Subbarao said. 																								 Mumbai, Oct. 29: Bombay High Court has restrained the income tax department from taking action on a show cause notice demanding capital gains tax from Vodafone Essar. A division bench of Justice F.I. Rebello and Justice J.P. Deodhar today restrained the department from pursuing the notice until the matter is heard on December 17.																								 Mundra Port, Oct. 29: Port operators DP World will invest $500 million in India by 2009. India is our main focus. In the next few years we will create infrastructure needed for the movement of cargo into the hinterland, executive vice-chairman Jamal Majid bin Thaniah said.
